**`find_threads_by_object` full-walks every thread on index miss.** When the comments-by-object index doesn't contain a hit, this function falls back to scanning every thread ref in the repository. For each thread, it first checks the tip commit's anchor, then does a full walk of all commits in the chain. This is O(threads * comments_per_thread) — for a large repo with thousands of comment threads, listing comments on a single object becomes extremely slow.

The fallback also has a subtle correctness issue: `tip_anchor_oid` only checks the *tip* commit, but if a thread was retargeted (reply with a different anchor), the tip might have a different anchor than earlier comments. The full walk catches this, but the early `continue` on tip match means a thread whose tip matches but also has comments on *other* objects will be included, while a thread whose tip doesn't match but has interior comments that do match will be walked redundantly.